WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.000
Ｔ Ｈ Ｅ
NIGHT AGENT
SEASON 01   #   EPISODE 04
"Eyes Only"

2
00:00:07.010 --> 00:00:10.090
ROSE: The Deputy Director of the FBI was just murdered <i>Godfather</i>-style.

3
00:00:10.090 --> 00:00:13.350
I'm not stepping into that White House and just handing over their drive.

4
00:00:13.350 --> 00:00:14.890
Not till we know who we can trust.

5
00:00:14.890 --> 00:00:17.100
[ ♪ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC ♪ ]

6
00:00:17.100 --> 00:00:18.730
You still have the hard drive?
- Yeah.

7
00:00:18.730 --> 00:00:21.480
That's priority 1. Peter. Where have you been?

8
00:00:23.230 --> 00:00:25.110
I found this on the air gap.

9
00:00:25.110 --> 00:00:28.150
The question now is. can you still convince me to trust you?

10
00:00:29.820 --> 00:00:32.160
There you are. I think I found something. Check this out.

11
00:00:32.160 --> 00:00:33.070
Rose. I...

12
00:00:33.070 --> 00:00:35.280
What the fuck is she doing here?
- She's on our side.

13
00:00:35.290 --> 00:00:38.960
ROSE: I heard my aunt say someone in the White House couldn't be trusted.

14
00:00:40.330 --> 00:00:41.830
How long have they worked for you?

15
00:00:41.830 --> 00:00:43.830
Him. over 8 years. Excellent results.

16
00:00:43.840 --> 00:00:46.420
He brought her in a couple of years ago. They make a good team.

17
00:00:47.010 --> 00:00:48.300
Wanna see our new home?

18
00:00:48.300 --> 00:00:49.760
What are you looking for here?

19
00:00:49.760 --> 00:00:52.890
I thought maybe we'll try this for a little while.

20
00:00:52.890 --> 00:00:54.220
See what it's like.

21
00:00:54.220 --> 00:00:55.850
Play house with me.

22
00:00:55.850 --> 00:00:57.310
I'm sending a replacement.

23
00:00:57.310 --> 00:00:58.270
<i>Erik Monks.</i>

24
00:00:58.270 --> 00:01:01.020
I wanted to introduce you to a new member of the security team.

25
00:01:01.020 --> 00:01:02.900
This is Erik. Erik. Maddie Redfield.

26
00:01:02.900 --> 00:01:05.650
You may have heard of him. He saved the last President years ago.

27
00:01:05.650 --> 00:01:07.610
You're the guy who got shot?
- Yes. ma'am.

28
00:01:07.610 --> 00:01:09.230
How'd a guy who saved POTUS...

29
00:01:09.240 --> 00:01:11.400
get stuck on the Vice President's daughter's detail?

30
00:01:11.400 --> 00:01:14.660
Physical therapy. It. uh. it took a while after I got shot.

31
00:01:14.660 --> 00:01:17.450
I guess this is their way of easing an old man back in.

32
00:01:17.450 --> 00:01:18.660
CHELSEA: I need a favor.

33
00:01:18.660 --> 00:01:20.330
I need to know why a national hero...

34
00:01:20.330 --> 00:01:23.420
got assigned to the most thankless detail in the whole Secret Service.

35
00:01:23.470 --> 00:01:36.470
Ｔ Ｈ Ｅ
NIGHT AGENT
SEASON 01   #   EPISODE 04
"Eyes Only"

36
00:01:36.930 --> 00:01:39.330
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]
- WOMAN: <i>Daredevil arriving now.</i>

37
00:01:39.680 --> 00:01:41.230
Copy that. Floor is clear.

38
00:01:41.230 --> 00:01:43.230
WOMAN: <i>Got some interference. Go again.</i>

39
00:01:43.230 --> 00:01:45.850
Floor is clear.

40
00:01:45.860 --> 00:01:47.520
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

41
00:01:47.520 --> 00:01:49.690
[MACHINES WHIRRING]
- [OBJECTS CLATTERING]

42
00:01:51.530 --> 00:01:53.110
[CROWD APPLAUDING. CHEERING]

43
00:01:53.110 --> 00:01:56.740
WOMAN#2: Mr. President. thank you for supporting union workers.

44
00:01:58.120 --> 00:02:00.330
MAN: Mr. President. Nice to meet you. sir.

45
00:02:02.160 --> 00:02:04.040
MAN#2: Mr. President. over here!

46
00:02:04.040 --> 00:02:05.120
MAN#3: Mr. President!

47
00:02:05.130 --> 00:02:07.500
MAN#4: Mr. President. you're the only reason...

48
00:02:07.500 --> 00:02:09.920
that we're able to keep this facility stateside.

49
00:02:09.920 --> 00:02:12.210
Every worker here would like to shake your hand.

50
00:02:12.220 --> 00:02:14.880
MAN#5: Thank you. Mr. President!
- Eyes on the beard at 12 o'clock.

51
00:02:14.880 --> 00:02:16.140
WOMAN: <i>Monks. your radio...</i>

52
00:02:16.140 --> 00:02:18.850
PRESIDENT: Thank you. Thank you. everyone.

53
00:02:18.850 --> 00:02:21.060
This is what American-made looks like.

54
00:02:21.060 --> 00:02:23.180
Keep up the great work.
- [ ♪ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC ♪ ]

55
00:02:23.180 --> 00:02:25.520
PRESIDENT: You know. when I was a boy...

56
00:02:25.520 --> 00:02:28.770
a union job at the plant meant honest hours...

57
00:02:28.770 --> 00:02:32.360
The guy with the beard. Someone check out what he's doing.

58
00:02:32.360 --> 00:02:33.570
WOMAN: <i>What was that?</i>

59
00:02:33.570 --> 00:02:35.110
ERIK: He's assembling something.

60
00:02:35.110 --> 00:02:38.200
It provides good wages. health. safety...

61
00:02:38.200 --> 00:02:39.580
ERIK: Gun!

62
00:02:39.580 --> 00:02:41.790
[CROWD GASPING. SCREAMING]

63
00:02:41.790 --> 00:02:43.540
[MEN GRUNTING]

64
00:02:44.120 --> 00:02:46.120
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

65
00:02:46.120 --> 00:02:48.210
[ ♪ INTENSE MUSIC ♪ ]

66
00:02:55.550 --> 00:02:57.260
[ ♪ OPENING THEME MUSIC ♪ ]

67
00:02:58.050 --> 00:03:00.720
[ERIK HUMMING]

68
00:03:06.390 --> 00:03:07.390
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

69
00:03:07.400 --> 00:03:08.310
Come in.

70
00:03:11.730 --> 00:03:12.860
[TOILET CLATTERING]

71
00:03:17.160 --> 00:03:19.570
[OBJECTS CLATTERING]

72
00:03:19.570 --> 00:03:21.700
Can I help you find something?
- CHELSEA: Pills.

73
00:03:22.370 --> 00:03:23.200
Why?

74
00:03:23.700 --> 00:03:24.950
You got a headache?

75
00:03:24.950 --> 00:03:27.960
I know you're an addict. I know they forced you into rehab...

76
00:03:27.960 --> 00:03:30.750
and I know that if you were anyone other than the boss's old partner...

77
00:03:30.750 --> 00:03:33.210
they'd never have put your ass back on a detail.

78
00:03:33.920 --> 00:03:36.510
I miss anything?
- No. you're mostly right.

79
00:03:37.260 --> 00:03:40.050
Getting shot. that started me on painkillers.

80
00:03:40.050 --> 00:03:42.260
It wouldn't look good to have me wash out...

81
00:03:42.260 --> 00:03:45.180
so they said if I stayed clean for a year. that I could...

82
00:03:45.180 --> 00:03:46.430
[SIGHING HEAVILY]

83
00:03:46.430 --> 00:03:47.940
...I could start back at the bottom.

84
00:03:47.940 --> 00:03:50.480
That's gotta be the biggest boys' club bullshit...

85
00:03:50.480 --> 00:03:51.520
I've ever heard.

86
00:03:52.730 --> 00:03:54.230
You said "mostly right."

87
00:03:54.980 --> 00:03:55.820
Yeah.

88
00:03:57.950 --> 00:04:00.030
You said I <i>was</i> an addict.

89
00:04:01.280 --> 00:04:03.280
I still am. Always will be.

90
00:04:03.280 --> 00:04:05.990
That supposed to make me feel any more confident in your abilities?

91
00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:08.580
It's not supposed to make you feel anything. It's the truth.

92
00:04:08.580 --> 00:04:11.250
It is also true that I am clean now.

93
00:04:11.250 --> 00:04:13.380
I get tested twice a week to prove it.

94
00:04:13.380 --> 00:04:16.630
The Vice President know an addict's protecting his daughter?

95
00:04:18.260 --> 00:04:19.510
I didn't think so.

96
00:04:21.430 --> 00:04:22.640
So tell him. then.

97
00:04:22.640 --> 00:04:24.720
[ ♪ DRAMATIC MUSIC ♪ ]

98
00:04:27.350 --> 00:04:28.890
Drum me out.

99
00:04:28.890 --> 00:04:30.850
All it takes is 1 phone call.

100
00:04:31.520 --> 00:04:33.610
Listen. you're ambitious.

101
00:04:34.860 --> 00:04:35.980
You wanna move up the ranks...

102
00:04:35.980 --> 00:04:38.030
and get on the President's detail one day. right?

103
00:04:38.530 --> 00:04:40.450
Well. maybe I can help you get there.

104
00:04:40.450 --> 00:04:42.660
How's that?
- I can teach you things.

105
00:04:42.660 --> 00:04:44.080
Teach me things?

106
00:04:45.120 --> 00:04:47.120
Like a mentor?
- Yeah.

107
00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:50.420
An old. slow. drug-addicted mentor?

108
00:04:51.370 --> 00:04:52.250
Yeah.

109
00:04:52.830 --> 00:04:56.670
I grew up around junkies in East St. Louis.

110
00:04:58.460 --> 00:05:00.510
My uncle. he went into recovery...

111
00:05:00.510 --> 00:05:03.590
found Jesus. got a job at the local supermarket...

112
00:05:03.590 --> 00:05:05.300
stayed sober until the day he died.

113
00:05:05.310 --> 00:05:09.560
Religion works for some people. meditation for others.

114
00:05:09.560 --> 00:05:11.230
It was the job that did it for him.

115
00:05:11.230 --> 00:05:12.770
I'm glad you got clean.

116
00:05:12.770 --> 00:05:14.560
Hope you stay clean.

117
00:05:14.560 --> 00:05:16.650
But you can't do this job for the wrong reasons.

118
00:05:16.650 --> 00:05:17.770
[DOOR OPENING]

119
00:05:17.780 --> 00:05:19.900
I don't disagree.
- Good.

120
00:05:20.490 --> 00:05:23.820
'Cause the stakes here are a lot fucking higher than "paper or plastic."

121
00:05:24.820 --> 00:05:25.740
[DOOR CLOSING]

122
00:05:28.290 --> 00:05:30.540
ROSE: Okay. let's just say I buy what you're selling.

123
00:05:30.540 --> 00:05:33.120
That means whoever had my aunt and uncle killed...

124
00:05:33.120 --> 00:05:35.210
did it because of what's on this hard drive.

125
00:05:35.210 --> 00:05:36.630
Which is exactly why I need it.

126
00:05:36.630 --> 00:05:37.750
Then what?

127
00:05:37.750 --> 00:05:40.840
Who could you possibly show it to if you can't trust anyone you work with?

128
00:05:40.840 --> 00:05:42.260
I can trust the President.

129
00:05:42.260 --> 00:05:43.840
You sure about that?

130
00:05:43.840 --> 00:05:47.260
President Travers has been my friend since she ran for state rep.

131
00:05:47.260 --> 00:05:50.640
We've worked together almost 23 years. I know exactly who she is.

132
00:05:50.640 --> 00:05:52.020
Think about the facts.

133
00:05:52.020 --> 00:05:53.810
Travers started the Night Action...

134
00:05:53.810 --> 00:05:57.060
she knew your aunt and uncle. requested them specifically.

135
00:05:57.070 --> 00:05:59.190
If anyone's on your side here. it's her.

136
00:05:59.190 --> 00:06:01.650
But if she hadn't put them on this Night Action. then...

137
00:06:01.650 --> 00:06:03.530
Then the truth would never have been found.

138
00:06:03.530 --> 00:06:05.570
Your aunt and uncle were patriots. Rose.

139
00:06:05.570 --> 00:06:08.120
They knew the risks associated with this assignment.

140
00:06:08.120 --> 00:06:09.950
Now we need to finish their work.

141
00:06:10.620 --> 00:06:11.580
I'll finish it. then.

142
00:06:11.580 --> 00:06:12.660
Excuse me?

143
00:06:12.660 --> 00:06:13.580
Me and Peter.

144
00:06:14.290 --> 00:06:15.460
Let us figure this out.

145
00:06:15.460 --> 00:06:19.380
It's the only way I'm gonna feel safe.
I'm not giving this hard drive to anyone.

146
00:06:19.380 --> 00:06:21.920
When we walked in. you said you found something. What?

147
00:06:21.920 --> 00:06:24.050
[ ♪ TENSE MUSIC ♪ ]

148
00:06:24.630 --> 00:06:26.550
An address.
- Address for what?

149
00:06:28.050 --> 00:06:31.350
How about this? I'm going to leave here without the drive.

150
00:06:31.350 --> 00:06:34.680
You 2 go to that address and find out whatever you can.

151
00:06:34.690 --> 00:06:38.110
In the meantime. I'll figure out how to present this plan to the President...

152
00:06:38.110 --> 00:06:40.610
in a way that doesn't sound incredibly reckless.

153
00:06:43.740 --> 00:06:44.780
Uh...

154
00:06:44.780 --> 00:06:47.070
does "Osprey" mean anything to you?

155
00:06:47.660 --> 00:06:50.450
Osprey? Like the bird? No. Why?

156
00:06:50.450 --> 00:06:55.330
I heard my uncle mention that he needed to warn Osprey.

157
00:06:55.330 --> 00:06:56.960
It must be a code name.

158
00:06:57.880 --> 00:06:59.290
Let me look into it.

159
00:07:00.750 --> 00:07:03.460
Don't let her out of your sight. not even for a minute.

160
00:07:03.460 --> 00:07:04.470
Yes. ma'am.

161
00:07:13.020 --> 00:07:15.020
[ ♪ SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC ♪ ]

162
00:07:17.650 --> 00:07:20.060
ROSE: Those 2 psychos are still coming for us.

163
00:07:20.570 --> 00:07:22.150
There are no tails. We're good.

164
00:07:22.150 --> 00:07:24.150
Why didn't you call me before you brought her?

165
00:07:24.150 --> 00:07:25.490
Why spring that on me?

166
00:07:25.490 --> 00:07:27.910
I couldn't risk the killers tracking you. okay?

167
00:07:28.530 --> 00:07:30.030
Well. I would have rather known.

168
00:07:30.030 --> 00:07:32.740
I got it. No more surprises.

169
00:07:35.160 --> 00:07:36.960
Find anything else on the drive?

170
00:07:36.960 --> 00:07:38.420
1.000s of files.

171
00:07:40.130 --> 00:07:41.960
What do you know about Omar Zadar?

172
00:07:41.960 --> 00:07:45.010
He's a Balkan dissident who heads up the People's Independence Front.

173
00:07:45.010 --> 00:07:48.470
When the PIF claimed responsibility for the metro attack. he denied it.

174
00:07:48.470 --> 00:07:51.220
Even Farr told me the President never bought that he was involved.

175
00:07:51.220 --> 00:07:52.220
What do you think?

176
00:07:52.970 --> 00:07:53.810
No idea.

177
00:07:54.560 --> 00:07:57.770
People say he's gone legit now that he's running for office. but...

178
00:07:58.270 --> 00:08:00.350
I mean. his group bombed buildings in the past. so...

179
00:08:00.350 --> 00:08:04.730
Either way. PIF. there was never any proof
they were involved in the metro attack.

180
00:08:04.730 --> 00:08:07.190
Maybe Emma and Henry found some evidence.

181
00:08:07.200 --> 00:08:10.530
There's a folder with his name on it on the drive.

182
00:08:10.530 --> 00:08:11.910
Any other names?

183
00:08:11.910 --> 00:08:14.700
Well. I did a search for "Farr" and "Hawkins." Nothing.

184
00:08:16.450 --> 00:08:17.460
Seems. uh...

185
00:08:18.540 --> 00:08:20.670
seems sort of weird that an engineering company...

186
00:08:20.670 --> 00:08:22.500
would be all the way out here. doesn't it?

187
00:08:25.250 --> 00:08:27.260
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

188
00:08:29.340 --> 00:08:31.180
[CICADAS CHITTERING]

189
00:08:31.180 --> 00:08:32.430
[CAR APPROACHING]

190
00:09:03.250 --> 00:09:04.170
Can I help you?

191
00:09:04.170 --> 00:09:06.800
Good morning. ma'am. I'm Peter Sutherland. This is...

192
00:09:06.800 --> 00:09:07.710
WOMAN: Hands.

193
00:09:08.210 --> 00:09:10.680
Excuse me?
- Show me your hands. please.

194
00:09:15.430 --> 00:09:18.060
Uh. do you know Emma and Henry Campbell?

195
00:09:18.060 --> 00:09:19.640
No. Should I?

196
00:09:19.640 --> 00:09:22.140
We were hoping to speak with an engineer who worked with them.

197
00:09:22.140 --> 00:09:24.940
We're investigating a...
- Uh. for a news article.

198
00:09:24.940 --> 00:09:27.530
Uh. we work with the <i>Richmond Daily News</i>.

199
00:09:28.110 --> 00:09:30.240
You got the wrong person. Sorry.

200
00:09:30.240 --> 00:09:32.110
Uh. wait. ma'am. please. If we could just ask...

201
00:09:32.110 --> 00:09:35.370
There is nothing you could ask that I would have any answers to.

202
00:09:35.370 --> 00:09:36.280
[ROSE GASPING]

203
00:09:36.870 --> 00:09:40.370
I live alone. I don't know any Ellas or Harrys...

204
00:09:41.080 --> 00:09:44.120
and I don't believe for a second this one here is a journalist.

205
00:09:44.130 --> 00:09:45.460
Now. please...

206
00:09:46.250 --> 00:09:48.000
turn around and be on your way.

207
00:09:50.300 --> 00:09:51.220
Come on.

208
00:10:00.470 --> 00:10:01.310
What?

209
00:10:04.900 --> 00:10:07.860
There is a rusted old wagon behind the barn. right?

210
00:10:08.440 --> 00:10:09.270
No.

211
00:10:09.280 --> 00:10:12.610
Well. there used to be?
- I don't know what you're talking about.

212
00:10:12.610 --> 00:10:15.610
I came here as a kid. I... I rode a pony over that ridge.

213
00:10:15.620 --> 00:10:18.990
I fell over. and I hurt my ankle. and I cried...

214
00:10:18.990 --> 00:10:23.580
and I made magic cookie bars with my Aunt Emma and another woman.

215
00:10:25.370 --> 00:10:26.250
Was that you?

216
00:10:26.750 --> 00:10:28.750
[ ♪ TENSE MUSIC ♪ ]

217
00:10:29.590 --> 00:10:30.750
Were you followed?

218
00:10:30.760 --> 00:10:31.670
No.

219
00:10:35.090 --> 00:10:36.260
Come inside. then.

220
00:10:42.600 --> 00:10:44.180
Take off your shoes.

221
00:10:44.190 --> 00:10:45.190
House rule.

222
00:10:46.440 --> 00:10:47.400
[DOOR CREAKING]

223
00:10:49.070 --> 00:10:51.900
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

224
00:10:54.450 --> 00:10:55.320
I'm Rose.

225
00:10:55.320 --> 00:10:56.240
I know.

226
00:10:56.240 --> 00:10:57.200
Lorna.

227
00:11:00.410 --> 00:11:05.000
NARRATOR: <i>The hyena is one of the more curious residents of the Savannah.</i>

228
00:11:08.420 --> 00:11:10.790
Why did you say you didn't know Emma and Henry?

229
00:11:10.800 --> 00:11:12.710
Why did you say you were reporters?

230
00:11:12.710 --> 00:11:14.710
Actually. I'm an FBI Agent.

231
00:11:14.720 --> 00:11:15.970
No shit.

232
00:11:15.970 --> 00:11:17.510
What a shock.

233
00:11:17.510 --> 00:11:19.640
When was the last time that you saw them?

234
00:11:19.640 --> 00:11:20.890
It's been years. Why?

235
00:11:21.600 --> 00:11:23.640
They were murdered 3 days ago.

236
00:11:26.770 --> 00:11:28.230
Where?
- In their home.

237
00:11:29.730 --> 00:11:32.530
I was there too. I barely made it out.

238
00:11:33.150 --> 00:11:34.280
I hadn't heard.

239
00:11:34.280 --> 00:11:37.200
PETER: Really? It's been all over the news.

240
00:11:37.200 --> 00:11:40.070
I stopped watching what passes for the news a while ago.

241
00:11:40.070 --> 00:11:41.370
How did you escape?

242
00:11:41.370 --> 00:11:42.540
I had help.

243
00:11:43.790 --> 00:11:44.700
I'm so sorry.

244
00:11:45.710 --> 00:11:47.670
Emma and Henry...
- I know they were spies.

245
00:11:48.250 --> 00:11:51.840
We found one of their hard drives. and some of the files led us here.

246
00:11:52.670 --> 00:11:55.840
The dates suggest that you were in touch.
- And?

247
00:11:55.840 --> 00:11:59.130
Ma'am. you may not be aware of this. This is a matter of national security.

248
00:11:59.140 --> 00:12:00.840
Is that right?
- PETER: Yes.

249
00:12:00.850 --> 00:12:03.300
Well. in that case. I will tell you my whole life story.

250
00:12:03.310 --> 00:12:05.600
You think maybe you could remove the sidearm...

251
00:12:05.600 --> 00:12:07.180
before coming into my house...

252
00:12:07.180 --> 00:12:10.060
and lecturing me about national fucking security?

253
00:12:11.360 --> 00:12:13.770
It's fine. I'm just... I'm just making a point.

254
00:12:13.770 --> 00:12:16.360
Which is?
- You've no idea what you're getting into.

255
00:12:16.360 --> 00:12:18.070
So tell us. please.

256
00:12:18.070 --> 00:12:19.530
The only thing I'm certain of...

257
00:12:19.530 --> 00:12:21.820
is the more you know. the more dangerous this becomes.

258
00:12:21.820 --> 00:12:22.910
We're past that. okay?

259
00:12:22.910 --> 00:12:25.490
We know someone in the White House has turned traitor.

260
00:12:25.490 --> 00:12:29.080
Whoever that is. we know that they were part of the metro bombing...

261
00:12:29.960 --> 00:12:31.040
and we think that...

262
00:12:31.790 --> 00:12:33.500
another attack is about to happen.

263
00:12:34.710 --> 00:12:37.380
So. please. if... if they said anything to you...

264
00:12:37.380 --> 00:12:38.300
They didn't.

265
00:12:38.300 --> 00:12:41.550
My job was to collect the intel. not analyze it.

266
00:12:42.680 --> 00:12:44.350
I'm supposed to be retired.

267
00:12:44.970 --> 00:12:46.510
But then again. so were they.

268
00:12:46.520 --> 00:12:48.140
What kind of intel were they after?

269
00:12:48.770 --> 00:12:50.020
Blueprints.

270
00:12:50.020 --> 00:12:52.100
Public infrastructure. building permits.

271
00:12:52.100 --> 00:12:54.860
I used to be a civil engineer. so I had the contacts.

272
00:12:54.860 --> 00:12:57.530
I don't know why they needed it. I knew not to ask.

273
00:12:57.530 --> 00:13:01.240
But you must have noticed something. like a pattern. or. like. a detail.

274
00:13:01.240 --> 00:13:03.780
Why?
- You're the only lead we have left.

275
00:13:04.370 --> 00:13:06.410
Look. I've been on the run for 3 days.

276
00:13:06.410 --> 00:13:09.830
The people who killed my aunt and uncle. they're after me now.

277
00:13:10.920 --> 00:13:13.120
Please just tell us something. anything.

278
00:13:13.130 --> 00:13:14.790
[ ♪ DRAMATIC MUSIC ♪ ]

279
00:13:15.460 --> 00:13:17.050
They were wonderful friends.

280
00:13:18.630 --> 00:13:19.590
Loyal.

281
00:13:23.010 --> 00:13:26.300
The files I supplied dealt with city services...

282
00:13:26.310 --> 00:13:27.970
but there were other files they wanted.

283
00:13:27.970 --> 00:13:30.640
Schematics of buildings. all in the same block.

284
00:13:30.640 --> 00:13:31.560
Where?

285
00:13:31.560 --> 00:13:33.480
You won't understand.
- What do you mean?

286
00:13:33.480 --> 00:13:36.110
I mean. you can't understand the files without me.

287
00:13:36.110 --> 00:13:37.980
They're complicated schematics.

288
00:13:38.570 --> 00:13:42.490
So... I guess we're going for a ride.

289
00:13:47.080 --> 00:13:48.740
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

290
00:13:59.880 --> 00:14:01.090
What are you drawing?

291
00:14:01.090 --> 00:14:02.220
A girl.

292
00:14:03.800 --> 00:14:05.220
A young woman. actually.

293
00:14:05.890 --> 00:14:08.140
Is it someone you know?

294
00:14:09.310 --> 00:14:11.270
MAN: Somebody I'd like to know better.

295
00:14:13.190 --> 00:14:15.810
MADDIE: Well. I'd love to see it when you're done.

296
00:14:15.810 --> 00:14:17.400
I'd be happy to show you...

297
00:14:18.570 --> 00:14:20.070
when I'm done.

298
00:14:22.440 --> 00:14:23.740
[BRUSHES CLATTERING]

299
00:14:23.740 --> 00:14:25.660
[MADDIE SIGHING]

300
00:14:28.450 --> 00:14:29.290
[MAN SIGHING]

301
00:14:34.000 --> 00:14:35.250
How's it coming?

302
00:14:37.460 --> 00:14:38.540
I don't know.

303
00:14:41.300 --> 00:14:42.550
Might need some help.

304
00:14:44.260 --> 00:14:46.220
You don't need any help.

305
00:14:46.930 --> 00:14:48.510
A little encouragement. maybe.

306
00:14:50.260 --> 00:14:51.350
Um...

307
00:14:52.810 --> 00:14:56.810
I'm not quite sure about the colors.

308
00:14:57.350 --> 00:14:59.020
Don't 2ⁿᵈ-guess yourself.

309
00:15:02.320 --> 00:15:03.900
I like this bit here.

310
00:15:05.570 --> 00:15:07.160
You do?
- Yeah.

311
00:15:09.830 --> 00:15:12.700
Well. what do you like most about it?

312
00:15:15.210 --> 00:15:16.120
The layering.

313
00:15:18.790 --> 00:15:19.710
[WHISPERING] The. uh...

314
00:15:20.880 --> 00:15:22.130
the brushstrokes.

315
00:15:24.010 --> 00:15:25.010
The you in it.

316
00:15:32.770 --> 00:15:36.770
You have incredible instincts. Maddie.

317
00:15:38.560 --> 00:15:39.730
Trust them.

318
00:15:53.990 --> 00:15:55.330
I'm sorry.

319
00:15:55.330 --> 00:15:58.040
Why?
- It was inappropriate of me.

320
00:15:58.040 --> 00:15:59.250
No. it's not.

321
00:15:59.750 --> 00:16:01.750
[BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY]

322
00:16:03.670 --> 00:16:05.670
God. this... this is a mistake.

323
00:16:07.590 --> 00:16:09.260
I shouldn't have. okay?

324
00:16:09.760 --> 00:16:11.140
Uh. I'm... I'm sorry.

325
00:16:14.060 --> 00:16:16.060
[ ♪ TENSE MUSIC ♪ ]

326
00:16:21.520 --> 00:16:23.520
I met them at Middlebury College.

327
00:16:24.150 --> 00:16:25.400
Middlebury?

328
00:16:25.400 --> 00:16:26.990
My aunt went to Vassar.

329
00:16:26.990 --> 00:16:29.650
This was the summer language program at Mid.

330
00:16:29.660 --> 00:16:33.120
Emma was in my Russian intensive. Henry was taking Arabic.

331
00:16:33.120 --> 00:16:35.490
I don't know exactly when they joined the FBI...

332
00:16:35.490 --> 00:16:38.710
but I do know they were recruited as a team.

333
00:16:38.710 --> 00:16:40.750
After that summer. we went our own ways.

334
00:16:40.750 --> 00:16:43.170
I had a normal career...

335
00:16:44.210 --> 00:16:46.920
but after doing some side work for them. they made some introductions.

336
00:16:46.920 --> 00:16:50.010
I carved out a niche in intelligence gathering.

337
00:16:50.010 --> 00:16:52.180
Wait. my... my aunt spoke Russian?

338
00:16:52.800 --> 00:16:53.800
Very well.

339
00:16:53.800 --> 00:16:56.970
She even recruited a couple of Russians to our side.

340
00:16:56.970 --> 00:16:58.560
You didn't hear that from me.

341
00:16:58.560 --> 00:16:59.850
This is crazy.

342
00:16:59.850 --> 00:17:01.140
They acted like nobodies...

343
00:17:01.150 --> 00:17:04.310
who went to garage sales and took cruises every summer.

344
00:17:04.310 --> 00:17:06.530
They weren't on cruises.

345
00:17:07.110 --> 00:17:09.900
So their whole life was a lie?

346
00:17:09.900 --> 00:17:10.950
Not a lie.

347
00:17:10.950 --> 00:17:12.070
A secret.

348
00:17:12.070 --> 00:17:14.370
One that allows you to see things differently...

349
00:17:14.370 --> 00:17:15.620
empowers you.

350
00:17:16.790 --> 00:17:17.700
It's important work.

351
00:17:17.700 --> 00:17:20.330
But no one knows who you really are. What kind of life is that?

352
00:17:20.330 --> 00:17:22.080
The kind that's fucking great.

353
00:17:27.300 --> 00:17:31.220
Does the. uh. code name Osprey mean anything to you?

354
00:17:32.180 --> 00:17:33.010
No.

355
00:17:34.220 --> 00:17:36.300
Okay.
- How did you get mixed up in all this?

356
00:17:36.310 --> 00:17:38.020
Oh. he works in the White House.

357
00:17:38.600 --> 00:17:43.140
When I called the emergency number my uncle gave me. Peter answered.

358
00:17:43.150 --> 00:17:44.730
White-glove service.

359
00:17:44.730 --> 00:17:46.690
I'm just a guy who answers the phone.

360
00:17:46.690 --> 00:17:51.530
Uh-huh. So Pete Sutherland's boy works the Night Action line.

361
00:17:53.530 --> 00:17:54.700
Wait. you knew my father?

362
00:17:54.700 --> 00:17:55.620
No.

363
00:17:56.780 --> 00:17:59.540
But you were on the metro that night?
- Yeah.

364
00:17:59.540 --> 00:18:00.580
Yeah. I was.

365
00:18:02.000 --> 00:18:03.420
Take the next exit.

366
00:18:10.960 --> 00:18:12.170
This is the place.

367
00:18:12.170 --> 00:18:14.510
Something either happened or is gonna happen on this block.

368
00:18:14.510 --> 00:18:16.340
At least Emma and Henry thought so.

369
00:18:16.350 --> 00:18:17.510
[CAR HORNS HONKING]

370
00:18:17.510 --> 00:18:18.970
PETER: No obvious targets.

371
00:18:19.470 --> 00:18:21.810
Are there any government buildings around here. contractors?

372
00:18:21.810 --> 00:18:22.730
LORNA: No.

373
00:18:22.730 --> 00:18:24.770
[SIREN WAILING]

374
00:18:24.770 --> 00:18:26.190
Can we get off the street?

375
00:18:26.190 --> 00:18:28.360
It doesn't feel safe out here.

376
00:18:28.360 --> 00:18:29.690
There's a café.

377
00:18:29.690 --> 00:18:32.570
I'll walk you through the files. See if we can figure out what they mean.

378
00:18:32.570 --> 00:18:34.490
I'll meet you guys back here in 10 minutes.

379
00:18:34.490 --> 00:18:36.660
I'm gonna have a look around.
- Good thinking.

380
00:18:37.870 --> 00:18:40.330
This portion of the grid covers this area.

381
00:18:40.330 --> 00:18:41.910
There's the nearest hub.

382
00:18:41.910 --> 00:18:45.460
Why would my aunt and uncle want intel on power grids and gas lines?

383
00:18:45.460 --> 00:18:48.000
Searching for vulnerabilities.

384
00:18:48.000 --> 00:18:49.710
Sabotage targets. maybe.

385
00:18:50.420 --> 00:18:53.630
But what's important enough to be a target around here?

386
00:18:54.130 --> 00:18:54.970
Got me.

387
00:18:55.470 --> 00:18:57.300
Okay. what's "video footage"?

388
00:18:57.300 --> 00:18:58.850
That's not mine. Gimme.

389
00:18:59.560 --> 00:19:00.510
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

390
00:19:00.510 --> 00:19:02.220
Looks like traffic cameras.

391
00:19:02.220 --> 00:19:03.680
Security footage.

392
00:19:03.680 --> 00:19:06.270
There's a folder for every address on the block.

393
00:19:06.270 --> 00:19:08.110
There's even one for this place.

394
00:19:11.980 --> 00:19:13.990
Okay. What were they looking for?

395
00:19:15.610 --> 00:19:16.910
How long have you known him?

396
00:19:17.570 --> 00:19:20.450
Peter? Um. just a few days.

397
00:19:20.450 --> 00:19:22.160
You know about his father. right?

398
00:19:22.160 --> 00:19:23.870
And what he was accused of?

399
00:19:24.370 --> 00:19:26.790
Some. Why?
- You don't think it's strange?

400
00:19:27.330 --> 00:19:30.460
He was on the metro when the bomb blew. now he's investigating it.

401
00:19:31.040 --> 00:19:31.920
So? [CHUCKLING]

402
00:19:31.920 --> 00:19:34.460
So... search the drive for his name.

403
00:19:34.460 --> 00:19:35.840
Why?

404
00:19:35.840 --> 00:19:37.630
Because I don't like coincidences.

405
00:19:37.630 --> 00:19:38.970
Neither should you.

406
00:19:40.220 --> 00:19:41.970
Okay.
- [KEYBOARD CLACKING]

407
00:19:41.970 --> 00:19:43.470
[DOOR OPENING]

408
00:19:43.470 --> 00:19:44.680
Hey. You find anything?

409
00:19:45.680 --> 00:19:47.440
[DOOR CLOSING]
- No. You?

410
00:19:47.440 --> 00:19:50.560
Just a dentist office. some accountant buildings. Nothing.

411
00:19:52.400 --> 00:19:53.320
Everything okay?

412
00:19:53.320 --> 00:19:54.570
Yeah. Oh!

413
00:19:55.360 --> 00:19:58.570
Uh. would you mind getting some paper towels from the bathroom?

414
00:19:59.160 --> 00:20:01.120
Yeah. of course.
- Man. I'm such a...

415
00:20:04.290 --> 00:20:05.950
That was a bit dramatic.

416
00:20:06.460 --> 00:20:08.250
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

417
00:20:12.250 --> 00:20:13.090
Nothing.

418
00:20:13.710 --> 00:20:14.710
Feel better?

419
00:20:14.710 --> 00:20:15.760
Maybe.

420
00:20:16.510 --> 00:20:17.340
You?

421
00:20:18.930 --> 00:20:20.720
[DOOR SQUEAKING]

422
00:20:25.390 --> 00:20:27.600
[LOW RUMBLING]

423
00:20:27.600 --> 00:20:29.690
[ ♪ TENSE MUSIC ♪ ]

424
00:20:30.400 --> 00:20:32.520
Excuse me. Is that the metro I just felt?

425
00:20:32.520 --> 00:20:34.610
Yeah. Runs right underneath here.

426
00:20:37.950 --> 00:20:39.860
LORNA: Thanks.
- What if it was a mistake?

427
00:20:39.860 --> 00:20:40.780
What?

428
00:20:40.780 --> 00:20:42.160
The metro bombing.

429
00:20:43.330 --> 00:20:44.280
Look.

430
00:20:44.790 --> 00:20:46.620
The bomb detonated here. right?

431
00:20:46.620 --> 00:20:48.750
That's just because I stopped the train.

432
00:20:49.250 --> 00:20:51.080
What if it was meant to explode someplace else?

433
00:20:51.080 --> 00:20:52.000
What. like here?

434
00:20:53.210 --> 00:20:55.800
But there's no other metro stops nearby.

435
00:20:55.800 --> 00:20:58.760
Yeah. no stops. but the tunnel runs directly under Wilson Boulevard.

436
00:20:58.760 --> 00:21:00.800
I felt it shake the hell out of the bathroom.

437
00:21:00.800 --> 00:21:02.300
ROSE: Okay. what's the difference...

438
00:21:02.300 --> 00:21:05.890
between a bomb going off in one location versus another?

439
00:21:05.890 --> 00:21:08.480
Maybe it's closer to street level here.
- It isn't.

440
00:21:09.020 --> 00:21:11.020
Bring up the neighborhood schematics again.

441
00:21:12.810 --> 00:21:14.650
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

442
00:21:14.650 --> 00:21:18.780
Okay. there's a major gas line that bisects a train tunnel.

443
00:21:18.780 --> 00:21:21.400
If it did go off under here. what would happen?

444
00:21:21.410 --> 00:21:25.780
If something were to hit that gas main. it'd take out 2 full city blocks.

445
00:21:27.290 --> 00:21:28.700
But why here though?

446
00:21:28.700 --> 00:21:29.950
I don't know.

447
00:21:29.960 --> 00:21:33.080
When you got on the metro that night. you prevented something.

448
00:21:33.080 --> 00:21:35.840
You wanna know what this traitor in the White House is planning?

449
00:21:35.840 --> 00:21:39.340
You need to determine what they failed to accomplish a year ago here.

450
00:21:40.970 --> 00:21:43.470
Bro. You know you gotta pay for that map.

451
00:21:46.600 --> 00:21:48.640
Okay. what about...?

452
00:21:48.640 --> 00:21:50.480
That one is Charlotte.

453
00:21:51.690 --> 00:21:52.520
Harper.

454
00:21:52.520 --> 00:21:53.480
Harper.

455
00:21:54.150 --> 00:21:54.980
Harper. right.

456
00:21:54.980 --> 00:21:57.360
Badger can only take her in small doses.

457
00:21:57.360 --> 00:21:58.480
Me. even smaller.

458
00:22:01.950 --> 00:22:04.450
You blend right in. don't you?
- That's the idea.

459
00:22:05.910 --> 00:22:06.910
Badger likes you.

460
00:22:06.910 --> 00:22:08.990
Didn't your POTUS like you?

461
00:22:08.990 --> 00:22:10.580
Oh. he liked me fine.

462
00:22:10.580 --> 00:22:12.660
Never posted selfies with me.

463
00:22:14.120 --> 00:22:16.540
For a second. I thought you might be paying me a compliment.

464
00:22:16.540 --> 00:22:18.710
Everyone's got their own style.

465
00:22:18.710 --> 00:22:21.510
That's right. And my style is the reason I'm the only team leader.

466
00:22:21.510 --> 00:22:23.920
Maddie hasn't burned or gotten fired.

467
00:22:23.930 --> 00:22:26.680
It's not because I blend. It's because I understand her.

468
00:22:26.680 --> 00:22:28.930
I get it. You're her friend.

469
00:22:28.930 --> 00:22:31.770
It's not about being her friend. It's about being allowed in.

470
00:22:32.270 --> 00:22:34.600
Your methods might work with a 65-year-old President...

471
00:22:34.600 --> 00:22:36.940
whose every move is mapped out weeks in advance...

472
00:22:36.940 --> 00:22:39.940
but this is a 20-year-old impulsive college girl.

473
00:22:39.940 --> 00:22:42.860
Wanna protect her? You have to know her better than she knows herself.

474
00:22:42.860 --> 00:22:44.070
And you do?

475
00:22:44.070 --> 00:22:46.530
I know what she likes. what party she'll wanna go to...

476
00:22:46.530 --> 00:22:48.780
all her spoiled little friends...

477
00:22:48.780 --> 00:22:50.490
who's safe. who's sketchy.

478
00:22:50.490 --> 00:22:52.870
I know Harper's about to meet with her douchebag boyfriend...

479
00:22:52.870 --> 00:22:54.830
who once sent Maddie a dick pic.

480
00:22:55.670 --> 00:22:58.830
I guess I'm just more comfortable observing at a distance.

481
00:22:58.840 --> 00:23:01.090
Good. Then that's right where I'll keep you.

482
00:23:05.430 --> 00:23:07.260
You sure we can't drop you off?

483
00:23:07.260 --> 00:23:09.010
You don't wanna slow down for me.

484
00:23:10.560 --> 00:23:13.430
Always assume you're being followed. Keep pushing forward.

485
00:23:14.520 --> 00:23:16.100
Thank you for everything.

486
00:23:18.900 --> 00:23:20.400
They were so proud of you. Rosie.

487
00:23:22.900 --> 00:23:24.690
They told you that?
- And more.

488
00:23:26.660 --> 00:23:29.030
Maybe when this is over. I could come over and...

489
00:23:29.030 --> 00:23:30.370
Yeah. I would love that.

490
00:23:31.370 --> 00:23:32.450
ROSE: Okay.

491
00:23:33.500 --> 00:23:34.500
Wait. wait. wait.

492
00:23:36.580 --> 00:23:37.830
You knew him. didn't you?

493
00:23:40.170 --> 00:23:42.250
I'm sorry to put you on the spot. I just...

494
00:23:43.050 --> 00:23:44.090
I have so many questions.

495
00:23:44.090 --> 00:23:46.420
Questions. or doubts?

496
00:23:46.430 --> 00:23:49.430
The government kept everything about his case classified.

497
00:23:49.430 --> 00:23:50.470
If you know anything...

498
00:23:50.470 --> 00:23:53.010
I'm sorry. I did not know your father personally.

499
00:23:53.770 --> 00:23:56.020
But I knew 2 Agents who worked his case.

500
00:23:56.020 --> 00:23:57.520
So you think he's guilty?

501
00:23:57.520 --> 00:24:00.310
They certainly did.
- So why haven't I seen proof?

502
00:24:00.310 --> 00:24:02.480
If you did find proof. what would that change?

503
00:24:02.480 --> 00:24:03.400
Everything.

504
00:24:05.190 --> 00:24:06.400
The truth is everything to me.

505
00:24:06.400 --> 00:24:08.240
Truth? [SCOFFING]

506
00:24:09.990 --> 00:24:11.530
It can also bring pain.

507
00:24:11.530 --> 00:24:14.200
I suggest you stop worrying about him.

508
00:24:15.290 --> 00:24:16.160
Focus on her.

509
00:24:25.130 --> 00:24:26.420
Thank you.
- Yeah.

510
00:24:26.920 --> 00:24:28.260
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

511
00:24:28.760 --> 00:24:30.220
[CAR ENGINE STARTING]

512
00:24:33.720 --> 00:24:35.060
Hello?
- Yo. yo.

513
00:24:35.770 --> 00:24:38.100
The BOLO turned up the car you're looking for.

514
00:24:38.100 --> 00:24:40.440
Trooper spotted it parked in a residential neighborhood...

515
00:24:40.440 --> 00:24:42.020
<i>outside Silver Spring.</i>

516
00:24:42.020 --> 00:24:43.230
Is it abandoned?

517
00:24:43.230 --> 00:24:44.770
Unclear. Headed there now.

518
00:24:44.770 --> 00:24:47.360
